- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with finding maximum weighted cliques in graph data. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper mentions experiments on real social network data. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper proposes a measure of clique-ness and uses optimization methods to solve the problem. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper deals with finding patterns in potentially noisy data. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is less likely as the paper does not seem to deal with sound or audio data.
